Shows like this one are exactly why the average person has such a misunderstanding of how gravity and the universe works. Cassini did not dive straight into Saturn. If you're in orbit of a planet you cant just fly straight down into it, you have to get rid of your horizontal velocity, in respect to the body you're orbiting, in order to "dive" into it. Flying straight down at a planet you're orbiting will do nothing but alter your orbit, making it more elliptical, decreasing your perigee and increasing your apogee so to speak. This is why rockets dont fly straight up to space. They fly out the atmosphere, spin over to one side then increase their horizontal velocity in respect to the earth.
